cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving multilingual neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a simple iterative training procedure that leverages the duality of translations, which involves optimizing the model's performance, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The iterative training procedure involves retraining the multilingual network, which is a form of optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks, which is a form of deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using BLEU scores, which is a common metric in NLP and machine translation, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
